            ('Apoptosis differs from necrosis (injury-caused cell death) because apoptosis',
             ['is a controlled, programmed process that does not cause inflammation', 'releases all cellular contents into surrounding tissue', 'requires no signals to initiate', 'only occurs in prokaryotes']),
            ('A mutation that reduces cholesterol content in animal cell membranes would',
             ['make membranes less able to buffer fluidity changes with temperature', 'always increase fluidity', 'prevent all transport', 'have no effect on membrane function']),
            ('Channel proteins and carrier proteins both enable facilitated diffusion but differ in that',
             ['channel proteins form open pores while carriers change shape (conformational change) to move molecules', 'carrier proteins require ATP while channel proteins do not', 'channel proteins only move large molecules', 'they are found in different cell types']),
